{"title":"Curve Walmer Wide gravel bars get narrower also, add new BP bikepacking editions too","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/25/curve-walmer-wide-gravel-bars-get-narrower-also-add-new-bp-bikepacking-editions-too/","date":1635187331000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer narrow WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars, all-road\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143451/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-all-road.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276111\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Curve’s wildly wide <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/05/29/review-curve-walmer-bar-is-a-wide-or-super-wide-flared-dropbar-for-off-road-adventures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Walmer handlebars</a> get a couple of new, narrower size options for gravel and adventure riders looking for extra stability and control off-road, without getting out of hand. The bars keep the same beloved flare, but dial it back to 40cm or 43cm at the hoods for more ‘normal’ width. Curve calls them narrow Wide bars, if that makes sense to you.</p><p>There are also a couple new BP bikepacking specific versions for bolting on more adventure accessories.</p><h2>Curve Walmer narrow WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars</h2><p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Curve-Walmer-super-wide-flared-dropbars_gravel-bikepacking-adventure-alloy-drop-handlebar_singlespeed-mountain-bike-cockpit.jpg\"></p><p>We reviewed the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/05/29/review-curve-walmer-bar-is-a-wide-or-super-wide-flared-dropbar-for-off-road-adventures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ultra-wide Walmer bars</a> last summer as a unique and playful option to reshape the adventure cockpit of everything from gravel bikes to dropbar mountain bikes. And while their incredible max 75cm width (60cm at the hoods) outside puts a different spin on the fit &amp; feel of some bikes, even the narrowest 46cm bar at the time still measured up 61cm wide outside.</p><p>Curve always knew that was going to be too wide for many riders, so now they’ve added a couple narrower options, too.</p><h3>Tech details – narrower WIDE bars</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer narrow WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars, dimensions\" width=\"1950\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options.jpg 1950w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options-297x91.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options-800x246.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options-120x37.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options-768x236.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143447/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_narrow-WIDE-bar-options-1536x473.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1950px) 100vw, 1950px\"></a></p><p>Keeping the same general geometry as the originals, the two new 40 &amp; 43cm Walmer bars measure up outside to 55cm &amp; 58cm, respectively. See, that’s still pretty wide for a ‘narrow’ dropbar.</p><p>The new ‘narrower’ Walmers are still shaped from 6066 aluminum, with 29° flare to their compact drops, plus 7° backsweep on the tops to give them more of a MTB bar feel when sitting more upright.&nbsp;The smaller 31.8mm clamp bar sizes keep the same shallow 110mm drop, but extend forward a tad more to a 65mm reach to balance out bringing your hands closer together.</p><h3>New Wide BP bar options</h3><div id=\"attachment_276139\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276139\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars, new BP bikepacking \" width=\"1300\" height=\"1425\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking.jpg 1300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking-274x300.jpg 274w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking-800x877.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking-109x120.jpg 109w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143440/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_loaded-down-BP-bikepacking-768x842.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276139\">c. Curve</p></div><p>In addition to narrower Wide bars, Curve’s two new Walmer BP bars add more accessory mounting capabilities for bikepacking and adventure racing. The new 46BP &amp; 50BP bars more than double the width of the 31.8mm round clamping area on the tops of these two bar sizes, to provide more room to bolt-on accessories like bags, lights, computer mounts, bells, and aero bars… or anything else you can think of.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars, new BP bikepacking options, dimensions comparison\" width=\"1950\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options.jpg 1950w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options-297x122.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options-800x328.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options-120x49.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options-768x315.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143444/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-specific-size-options-1536x630.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1950px) 100vw, 1950px\"></a></p><p>For example, the new 46BP bar ends up with a ~190mm wide clamping area (vs. ~70mm standard) and the 50BP gets 240+mm (vs. ~110mm standard). Those appear to be about as much or more than on the giant 60cm bar I ride (see MTB photo,<em> at top</em>) which has plenty of room to attach anything I could imagine.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer WIDE&nbsp; gravel &amp; adventure bars, new BP bikepacking options\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143437/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_BP-bikepacking-version-more-mounting-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>The BP edition bars also get the same geometry as the new narrower bars, with 29° flare, 7° backsweep, 110mm drop, and the longer 65mm reach.</p><h3>Curve Walmer Wide dropbars – Pricing &amp; availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Walmer Wide gravel adventure dropbars\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/25143424/Curve-Walmer-wide-flared-alloy-adventure-gravel-dropbars_riding-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>No matter how wide you decide to go, all of the Walmers sell for the same AUS$189 (~$140/120€), which includes Curve’s extra-long rolls of grippy 3.2mm thick black bar tape. All sizes are available in stock now, and will reshape how you hold onto your all-road, gravel &amp; mountain bikes on your next adventure.</p><section><a href=\"https://www.curvecycling.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>CurveCycling.com.au</em></a></section></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e37ae7f2aa16d47355398003d5a97d63a9664eae548a3bc1b15d65249bb67674","category":"Cycling"}